{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_016zeU7ieGnrEjHLeDN2cApQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01G2qwrvR9G7LXZ63xRXuacu","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Create Jakarta EE config files","prompt":"I need you to create several configuration files for a Jakarta EE / WildFly migration. The working directory is:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output\n\n## 1. Create persistence.xml\nCreate file at: src/main/resources/META-INF/persistence.xml\n\nThe entities are:\n- org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.ApplicationSettings\n- org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo\n- org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Leg\n- org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent\n- org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location\n- org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage\n- org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.CarrierMovement\n\nContent should be:\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<persistence xmlns=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee\"\n             xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n             xsi:schemaLocation=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee/persistence_3_0.xsd\"\n             version=\"3.0\">\n    <persistence-unit name=\"cargo-tracker-pu\" transaction-type=\"JTA\">\n        <jta-data-source>java:jboss/datasources/CargoTrackerDS</jta-data-source>\n        <properties>\n            <property name=\"hibernate.hbm2ddl.auto\" value=\"create-drop\"/>\n            <property name=\"hibernate.show_sql\" value=\"true\"/>\n            <property name=\"hibernate.format_sql\" value=\"true\"/>\n            <property name=\"jakarta.persistence.sql-load-script-source\" value=\"import.sql\"/>\n        </properties>\n    </persistence-unit>\n</persistence>\n```\n\n## 2. Create beans.xml  \nCreate file at: src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/beans.xml\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<beans xmlns=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee\"\n       xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n       xsi:schemaLocation=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee/beans_4_0.xsd\"\n       version=\"4.0\"\n       bean-discovery-mode=\"all\">\n</beans>\n```\n\n## 3. Move web.xml from META-INF to webapp/WEB-INF\nRead src/main/resources/META-INF/web.xml, then write the same content to src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/web.xml\n\n## 4. Move faces-config.xml\nRead src/main/resources/META-INF/faces-config.xml, then write the same content to src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/faces-config.xml\n\n## 5. Move web resources from META-INF/resources to webapp\nUse bash to copy all files from:\n  src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/\nto:\n  src/main/webapp/\n\nIMPORTANT: Use the command:\n  cp -r /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/* /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/webapp/\n\nBut make sure to create src/main/webapp/ and src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/ first.\n\n## 6. Create WildFly standalone CLI commands file\nCreate file at: wildfly-config.cli with the following content for configuring H2 datasource and JMS queues:\n\n```\n# WildFly configuration script for Cargo Tracker\n# Runs before deployment\n\n# Add H2 datasource\n/subsystem=datasources/data-source=CargoTrackerDS:add(jndi-name=\"java:jboss/datasources/CargoTrackerDS\", connection-url=\"jdbc:h2:file:./cargo-tracker-data/cargo-tracker-database;AUTO_SERVER=TRUE\", driver-name=h2, user-name=sa, password=\"\")\n\n# Add JMS Queues\njms-queue add --queue-address=CargoHandledQueue --entries=java:/jms/queue/CargoHandledQueue\njms-queue add --queue-address=DeliveredCargoQueue --entries=java:/jms/queue/DeliveredCargoQueue\njms-queue add --queue-address=HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptQueue --entries=java:/jms/queue/HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptQueue\njms-queue add --queue-address=MisdirectedCargoQueue --entries=java:/jms/queue/MisdirectedCargoQueue\njms-queue add --queue-address=RejectedRegistrationAttemptsQueue --entries=java:/jms/queue/RejectedRegistrationAttemptsQueue\n```\n\n## 7. Update the application.properties\nThe existing application.properties has Quarkus-specific config. We need to keep it minimal for any code that reads it, or better yet, replace it with a minimal version. Write to src/main/resources/application.properties:\n\n```\n# Application configuration\napp.configuration.GraphTraversalUrl=http://localhost:8080/cargo-tracker/rest/graph-traversal/shortest-path\n```\n\n## 8. Keep the import.sql \nThe import.sql file at src/main/resources/import.sql should stay as is:\n```sql\nINSERT INTO ApplicationSettings (id, sampleLoaded) VALUES (1, FALSE);\n```\n\nDo all of these tasks. Read each existing file before writing to it. Create new directories as needed with mkdir -p.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":371,"cache_read_input_tokens":119612,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":371,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1695},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be751ba2-32a8-49a7-8b94-68e2cc55da12","uuid":"54ded056-0df8-4cf5-b474-1c316cf92b52"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I need you to create several configuration files for a Jakarta EE / WildFly migration. The working directory is:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output\n\n## 1. Create persistence.xml\nCreate file at: src/main/resources/META-INF/persistence.xml\n\nThe entities are:\n- org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.ApplicationSettings\n- org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo\n- org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Leg\n- org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent\n- org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location\n- org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage\n- org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.CarrierMovement\n\nContent should be:\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<persistence xmlns=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee\"\n             xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n             xsi:schemaLocation=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee/persistence_3_0.xsd\"\n             version=\"3.0\">\n    <persistence-unit name=\"cargo-tracker-pu\" transaction-type=\"JTA\">\n        <jta-data-source>java:jboss/datasources/CargoTrackerDS</jta-data-source>\n        <properties>\n            <property name=\"hibernate.hbm2ddl.auto\" value=\"create-drop\"/>\n            <property name=\"hibernate.show_sql\" value=\"true\"/>\n            <property name=\"hibernate.format_sql\" value=\"true\"/>\n            <property name=\"jakarta.persistence.sql-load-script-source\" value=\"import.sql\"/>\n        </properties>\n    </persistence-unit>\n</persistence>\n```\n\n## 2. Create beans.xml  \nCreate file at: src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/beans.xml\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<beans xmlns=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee\"\n       xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n       xsi:schemaLocation=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee/beans_4_0.xsd\"\n       version=\"4.0\"\n       bean-discovery-mode=\"all\">\n</beans>\n```\n\n## 3. Move web.xml from META-INF to webapp/WEB-INF\nRead src/main/resources/META-INF/web.xml, then write the same content to src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/web.xml\n\n## 4. Move faces-config.xml\nRead src/main/resources/META-INF/faces-config.xml, then write the same content to src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/faces-config.xml\n\n## 5. Move web resources from META-INF/resources to webapp\nUse bash to copy all files from:\n  src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/\nto:\n  src/main/webapp/\n\nIMPORTANT: Use the command:\n  cp -r /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/* /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/webapp/\n\nBut make sure to create src/main/webapp/ and src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/ first.\n\n## 6. Create WildFly standalone CLI commands file\nCreate file at: wildfly-config.cli with the following content for configuring H2 datasource and JMS queues:\n\n```\n# WildFly configuration script for Cargo Tracker\n# Runs before deployment\n\n# Add H2 datasource\n/subsystem=datasources/data-source=CargoTrackerDS:add(jndi-name=\"java:jboss/datasources/CargoTrackerDS\", connection-url=\"jdbc:h2:file:./cargo-tracker-data/cargo-tracker-database;AUTO_SERVER=TRUE\", driver-name=h2, user-name=sa, password=\"\")\n\n# Add JMS Queues\njms-queue add --queue-address=CargoHandledQueue --entries=java:/jms/queue/CargoHandledQueue\njms-queue add --queue-address=DeliveredCargoQueue --entries=java:/jms/queue/DeliveredCargoQueue\njms-queue add --queue-address=HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptQueue --entries=java:/jms/queue/HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptQueue\njms-queue add --queue-address=MisdirectedCargoQueue --entries=java:/jms/queue/MisdirectedCargoQueue\njms-queue add --queue-address=RejectedRegistrationAttemptsQueue --entries=java:/jms/queue/RejectedRegistrationAttemptsQueue\n```\n\n## 7. Update the application.properties\nThe existing application.properties has Quarkus-specific config. We need to keep it minimal for any code that reads it, or better yet, replace it with a minimal version. Write to src/main/resources/application.properties:\n\n```\n# Application configuration\napp.configuration.GraphTraversalUrl=http://localhost:8080/cargo-tracker/rest/graph-traversal/shortest-path\n```\n\n## 8. Keep the import.sql \nThe import.sql file at src/main/resources/import.sql should stay as is:\n```sql\nINSERT INTO ApplicationSettings (id, sampleLoaded) VALUES (1, FALSE);\n```\n\nDo all of these tasks. Read each existing file before writing to it. Create new directories as needed with mkdir -p."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G2qwrvR9G7LXZ63xRXuacu","session_id":"be751ba2-32a8-49a7-8b94-68e2cc55da12","uuid":"cd68f960-1b7d-4003-9261-7b3170c4652c"}
