{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LvexvsogG9fnEMe3fhBSrN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<web-app\n     3→    xmlns=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee\"\n     4→    xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     5→    xsi:schemaLocation=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee/web-app_6_0.xsd\"\n     6→    version=\"6.0\">\n     7→  <context-param>\n     8→    <param-name>jakarta.faces.PROJECT_STAGE</param-name>\n     9→    <param-value>Development</param-value>\n    10→  </context-param>\n    11→  <context-param>\n    12→    <param-name>jakarta.faces.CLIENT_WINDOW_MODE</param-name>\n    13→    <param-value>url</param-value>\n    14→  </context-param>\n    15→  <context-param>\n    16→    <param-name>primefaces.THEME</param-name>\n    17→    <param-value>saga</param-value>\n    18→  </context-param>\n    19→  <context-param>\n    20→    <param-name>primefaces.FONT_AWESOME</param-name>\n    21→    <param-value>true</param-value>\n    22→  </context-param>\n    23→  <context-param>\n    24→    <param-name>primefaces.MOVE_SCRIPTS_TO_BOTTOM</param-name>\n    25→    <param-value>true</param-value>\n    26→  </context-param>\n    27→  <mime-mapping>\n    28→    <extension>ttf</extension>\n    29→    <mime-type>application/font-sfnt</mime-type>\n    30→  </mime-mapping>\n    31→  <mime-mapping>\n    32→    <extension>woff</extension>\n    33→    <mime-type>application/font-woff</mime-type>\n    34→  </mime-mapping>\n    35→  <mime-mapping>\n    36→    <extension>woff2</extension>\n    37→    <mime-type>application/font-woff2</mime-type>\n    38→  </mime-mapping>\n    39→  <mime-mapping>\n    40→    <extension>eot</extension>\n    41→    <mime-type>application/vnd.ms-fontobject</mime-type>\n    42→  </mime-mapping>\n    43→  <servlet>\n    44→    <servlet-name>Faces Servlet</servlet-name>\n    45→    <servlet-class>jakarta.faces.webapp.FacesServlet</servlet-class>\n    46→    <load-on-startup>1</load-on-startup>\n    47→  </servlet>\n    48→  <servlet-mapping>\n    49→    <servlet-name>Faces Servlet</servlet-name>\n    50→    <url-pattern>*.xhtml</url-pattern>\n    51→  </servlet-mapping>\n    52→  <welcome-file-list>\n    53→    <welcome-file>index.xhtml</welcome-file>\n    54→    <welcome-file>index.html</welcome-file>\n    55→  </welcome-file-list>\n    56→</web-app>\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G2qwrvR9G7LXZ63xRXuacu","session_id":"be751ba2-32a8-49a7-8b94-68e2cc55da12","uuid":"260b54ab-f5ae-4559-97cb-92096902e0b8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MfgKm47zooLwVp84MrEjfx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<faces-config xmlns=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee\"\n     3→  xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\" version=\"2.3\"\n     4→  xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee/web-facesconfig_2_3.xsd\">\n     5→  <application>\n     6→    <action-listener>org.primefaces.application.DialogActionListener</action-listener>\n     7→    <navigation-handler>org.primefaces.application.DialogNavigationHandler</navigation-handler>\n     8→    <view-handler>org.primefaces.application.DialogViewHandler</view-handler>\n     9→  </application>\n    10→</faces-config>\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G2qwrvR9G7LXZ63xRXuacu","session_id":"be751ba2-32a8-49a7-8b94-68e2cc55da12","uuid":"afc96c88-ebd2-4cbc-9ce0-456e53a7ff79"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018hozaRGVACFXa13yBAuUft","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→quarkus.http.root-path=/cargo-tracker\n     2→\n     3→# configure your datasource\n     4→quarkus.datasource.db-kind=h2\n     5→quarkus.datasource.username=sa\n     6→quarkus.datasource.password=\n     7→quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:h2:file:./cargo-tracker-data/cargo-tracker-database\n     8→quarkus.datasource.jdbc.max-size=32\n     9→quarkus.datasource.jdbc.min-size=2\n    10→\n    11→%test.quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:h2:file:./cargo-tracker-test-data/cargo-tracker-database\n    12→\n    13→quarkus.hibernate-orm.schema-management.strategy=drop-and-create\n    14→quarkus.hibernate-orm.log.sql=true\n    15→quarkus.hibernate-orm.sql-load-script=import.sql\n    16→\n    17→# Configures the Qpid JMS properties.\n    18→quarkus.qpid-jms.url=amqp://localhost:5672\n    19→quarkus.qpid-jms.username=quarkus\n    20→quarkus.qpid-jms.password=quarkus\n    21→\n    22→# No authentication for test\n    23→%test.quarkus.qpid-jms.username=\n    24→%test.quarkus.qpid-jms.password=\n    25→\n    26→# app\n    27→app.configuration.GraphTraversalUrl=http://localhost:8080/cargo-tracker/rest/graph-traversal/shortest-path\n    28→# test app starts on port 8081\n    29→%test.app.configuration.GraphTraversalUrl=http://localhost:8081/cargo-tracker/rest/graph-traversal/shortest-path\n    30→\n    31→# JMS queues\n    32→app.jms.CargoHandledQueue=CargoHandledQueue\n    33→app.jms.DeliveredCargoQueue=DeliveredCargoQueue\n    34→app.jms.HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptQueue=HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptQueue\n    35→app.jms.MisdirectedCargoQueue=MisdirectedCargoQueue\n    36→app.jms.RejectedRegistrationAttemptsQueue=RejectedRegistrationAttemptsQueue\n    37→quarkus.arc.exclude-types=org.jberet.schedule.SchedulingJobListener\n    38→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G2qwrvR9G7LXZ63xRXuacu","session_id":"be751ba2-32a8-49a7-8b94-68e2cc55da12","uuid":"4460ab7f-f47e-4358-ab52-fe12ab9631e2"}
