{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Kw8VCrtwFMc1hWXxd3TNa5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Interesting! The container is running Payara Micro, not WildFly. The image seems to have been built from a different base. The issue is that the JMS consumers still have `@Inject private ConnectionFactory connectionFactory;` but they're now `@MessageDriven` beans, so they shouldn't be injecting ConnectionFactory directly. The MDB pattern with `@MessageDriven` means the container handles the connection.\n\nWait - I see the problem. I changed the consumers to `@MessageDriven` but the original Quarkus-migrated consumers also had `@Inject ConnectionFactory`. The `@MessageDriven` beans don't need that. But the error also says some consumers (like MisdirectedCargoConsumer) still inject ConnectionFactory.\n\nLet me check the actual deployed consumer code:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2736,"cache_read_input_tokens":142099,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2736,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":316},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be751ba2-32a8-49a7-8b94-68e2cc55da12","uuid":"7b524390-4e3b-44b3-a41d-f16cb87a517f"}
