{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LDEiFTxHEpvy6WpKyMGDtR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     5→import jakarta.ejb.ActivationConfigProperty;\n     6→import jakarta.ejb.MessageDriven;\n     7→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     8→import jakarta.jms.JMSException;\n     9→import jakarta.jms.Message;\n    10→import jakarta.jms.MessageListener;\n    11→\n    12→@MessageDriven(activationConfig = {\n    13→    @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"destinationLookup\", propertyValue = \"java:/jms/queue/MisdirectedCargoQueue\"),\n    14→    @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"destinationType\", propertyValue = \"jakarta.jms.Queue\")\n    15→})\n    16→public class MisdirectedCargoConsumer implements MessageListener {\n    17→\n    18→  @Inject\n    19→  private Logger logger;\n    20→\n    21→  @Override\n    22→  public void onMessage(Message message) {\n    23→    try {\n    24→      logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo with tracking ID {0} misdirected.\", message.getBody(String.class));\n    25→    } catch (JMSException ex) {\n    26→      logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"Error processing message.\", ex);\n    27→    }\n    28→  }\n    29→}\n    30→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be751ba2-32a8-49a7-8b94-68e2cc55da12","uuid":"57b579fc-4234-4ad4-8a59-f54a43fe07d6"}
