{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QSrnX96oXFj42qb2ZtqEik","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! All changes have been successfully applied. Let me create a summary of all the changes made:\n\n## Summary of Changes\n\nI have successfully fixed all deployment errors in the WildFly Jakarta EE application. Here's a detailed report of all changes made:\n\n### 1. **JmsApplicationEvents.java**\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/jms/JmsApplicationEvents.java`\n\n**Change:**\n- Changed `@Inject private ConnectionFactory connectionFactory;` to `@Resource(lookup = \"java:/ConnectionFactory\") private ConnectionFactory connectionFactory;`\n- This is required because ConnectionFactory in WildFly needs to be looked up via JNDI, not injected via CDI.\n\n### 2. **InitLoader.java**\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/InitLoader.java`\n\n**Changes:**\n- Added import: `import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;`\n- Changed `@Inject private EntityManager entityManager;` to `@PersistenceContext private EntityManager entityManager;`\n- EntityManager should use @PersistenceContext annotation for proper JPA injection in Jakarta EE.\n\n### 3. **TestDataGenerator.java**\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/test/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/TestDataGenerator.java`\n\n**Changes:**\n- Added import: `import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;`\n- Changed `@Inject private EntityManager entityManager;` to `@PersistenceContext private EntityManager entityManager;`\n- Same reason as InitLoader.java - proper JPA injection pattern.\n\n### 4. **EventLogger.java**\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/mobile/EventLogger.java`\n\n**Changes:**\n- Removed the injected field: `@Inject private FacesContext context;`\n- Changed the usage in the `validate()` method from `context.addMessage(null, message);` to `FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().addMessage(null, message);`\n- FacesContext is not CDI-injectable by default in Jakarta EE/WildFly. The proper approach is to use `FacesContext.getCurrentInstance()` to get the current instance.\n\n### 5. **JMS Consumer Files - No Changes Needed**\nI checked all the JMS consumer files and confirmed they do NOT have `@Inject ConnectionFactory`:\n- CargoHandledConsumer.java - No ConnectionFactory injection\n- DeliveredCargoConsumer.java - No ConnectionFactory injection\n- HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptConsumer.java - No ConnectionFactory injection\n- MisdirectedCargoConsumer.java - No ConnectionFactory injection\n- RejectedRegistrationAttemptsConsumer.java - No ConnectionFactory injection\n\nThese files are Message-Driven Beans (MDBs) and don't need to inject ConnectionFactory since they receive messages passively.\n\n### Summary of Error Types Fixed:\n1. **ConnectionFactory injection** - Changed from `@Inject` to `@Resource(lookup = \"java:/ConnectionFactory\")` (1 file)\n2. **EntityManager injection** - Changed from `@Inject` to `@PersistenceContext` (2 files)\n3. **FacesContext injection** - Removed `@Inject` and replaced with `FacesContext.getCurrentInstance()` (1 file)\n\nAll files have been successfully modified and should now deploy correctly on WildFly without the previous injection-related errors."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be751ba2-32a8-49a7-8b94-68e2cc55da12","uuid":"c474febd-4eca-4548-b56e-d2e9cfaae096"}
