{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Cau1vE5m7xhHXia9VWBxqF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The container is running **Open Liberty** instead of **WildFly**! The Docker image is based on `maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble` which seems to have changed behavior, or the previous WildFly build worked differently. There are two issues:\n\n1. **H2 URL format error** - the datasource URL is empty/wrong\n2. **@Transactional on EJB error** - `@Transactional` is not allowed on EJB beans (UploadDirectoryScanner)\n\nWait - looking more carefully, the logs show \"Open Liberty\" not WildFly. This means the container didn't actually start WildFly. Let me check if WildFly is the CMD:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1948,"cache_read_input_tokens":47547,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1948,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":260},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be751ba2-32a8-49a7-8b94-68e2cc55da12","uuid":"775a44fe-f209-4702-bbb6-e67900a2709a"}
